cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper introduces an evolutionary algorithm designed to optimize for evolvability, which is related to the field of neural evolution (cs.NE). The algorithm involves optimizing for diversity of behaviors exhibited under random mutations, which is a machine learning optimization problem (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential of evolvable representations for deep neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve locomotion tasks, which are related to robotics (cs.SY) and control systems (cs.RO).
